  <name>Deadbolt</name>
  <summary>Dead-simple file encryption for any OS</summary>

  <developer id="alichtman">
    <name>Aaron Lichtman</name>
  </developer>

  <description>
    <p>
      Deadbolt is a simple, cross-platform file encryption tool using AES-256-GCM
      and Argon2id key derivation. Files can be encrypted or decrypted by
      drag-and-drop or double-click, with no configuration required.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>AES-256-GCM authenticated encryption</li>
      <li>Argon2id key derivation (RFC 9106 first recommended parameters)</li>
      <li>Drag-and-drop or double-click to encrypt/decrypt</li>
      <li>Standalone CLI available</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

